And so, you know, in terms of what's unique about a Nita cell in comparison to Ida cell and Cilta cell, you know, what's thought to be part of the potentially unique characteristics is the the synthetic D domain binder.

00:00:43.140 --> 00:00:54.740
So it's smaller than the the murine, you know, construct of Ida cell or the camelid bivalent heavy chain constructs with Carvicti.

00:00:54.960 --> 00:00:58.360
And essentially that smaller, you know, sort of.

00:00:59.160 --> 00:01:20.800
Linker is thought to help or binder is thought to help to contribute to higher transduction efficiency, greater percentage of car positivity, lower cell dose being able to be administered, less tonic signaling and, you know, a fast off rate combined with high surface expression, which may allow good cell killing while less, you know, having less prolonged inflammation potentially.

00:01:20.800 --> 00:01:28.800
So but the initial indication of the potentially potent effectiveness of an Ida cell came in the phase one study, which, you know, evaluated.

00:01:29.160 --> 00:01:53.220
The patient's four plus prior lines of therapy and showed a medium progression free survival amongst these patients of about 30 months, you know, about an 80% CRSCR rate and importantly, you know, gave the first indication that there were no signals for non-ICANN's neurotoxicity, including Parkinsonism, cranial neuropalsy, Guillain-Barre being observed in these patients.

00:01:53.680 --> 00:01:56.360
So that led to the Imagine One phase two trial.

00:01:56.660 --> 00:01:58.520
You know, this was a relatively straightforward design.

00:01:58.700 --> 00:01:59.140
You know, patients.

00:01:59.160 --> 00:02:04.180
Needed to have three or more prior lines of therapy, including an image, a PI, a CD38 monoclonal antibody.

00:02:05.020 --> 00:02:09.580
They underwent leukapheresis and then manufacturing bridging was strongly encouraged.

00:02:09.940 --> 00:02:24.220
And then, you know, lymphodepletion followed by cell administration target dose of 115 times 10 to the six car cells, 129 patients, leukapheresis, 118 got LD, LDC, and then all but one got cells.

00:02:24.920 --> 00:02:28.580
Median follow up in this presentation was about 16 months from administration.

