You know, and what is different is the median number of prior lines of therapy.

00:02:53.760 --> 00:02:58.360
But what's a little bit similar is the, you know, sort of the class exposures that patients have.

00:02:58.700 --> 00:03:08.000
You know, so basically patients who are enrolled in 2023 were packing a lot more into their lines, their three lines of therapy than we were packing into lines of therapy in 2019.

00:03:08.480 --> 00:03:19.680
So, you know, very pretty kind of strikingly similar amount of triple class refractory 88 versus 87% of patients, penta refractory 42 versus 41 and characteristics like extramedullary disease rates.

00:03:20.280 --> 00:03:27.460
So, you know, what, what, what happens when you put these cells into people is that everybody responds, you know, 96% overall response rate.

00:03:27.880 --> 00:03:28.680
You know, time.

